Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced) into half moons. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Peel the @carrot{2}(peeled, top and bottom removed, halved lengthways and sliced into thin half moons). Put the @British turkey steaks{2} between two sheets of #clingfilm{} and bash with a #rolling pin{} until 1cm thick. Tip the @crème fraîche{1} in one #shallow bowl{} with a pinch of @salt{} and @black pepper{} and the @panko breadcrumbs{50%g} in another.

Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #large saucepan{} on high heat with the @star anise{1} and half the @chicken stock pot{1/2}. Once the water is boiling, add the @basmati rice{150%g} and stir. Bring back to the boil, pop a #lid{} on the pan, turn the heat to medium-low and cook for ~{10%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat and leave for another ~{10%minutes} with the lid on.

> TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Put a splash of @oil{} in another large saucepan on medium heat and add the onion. Cook until soft, ~{5%minutes}. Then add the carrot, a pinch of @salt{} and a good grind of @black pepper{}. Stir and cook for a further ~{5%minutes}. Add in the garlic, @curry powder mix{1.5} and @plain flour{24%g}. Stir and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @water{300%ml} to the pan along with the remaining @chicken stock pot{1/2}, the @honey{1} and @soy sauce{1.5}. Stir continuously and bring to a simmer. Cook until the sauce is thick and the carrots are tender, ~{10%minutes}. Take off the heat, stir in the @baby spinach{1} and allow it to wilt. Pop a lid on and set aside.

Meanwhile, spread each turkey steak with a spoonful of the seasoned crème fraîche. You want a thin layer on each side, just enough so the breadcrumbs can stick. Transfer the turkey to the bowl of breadcrumbs and coat both sides. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, lay in the turkey and cook until golden brown on one side, ~{3-4%minutes}. Turn carefully and cook the other side, another ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the turkey is ready, carefully transfer it to a #chopping board{}. Slice into 1cm wide strips. Remove the star anise from the rice and fluff it up with a #fork{}. Serve in bowls with the curry sauce spooned over and the turkey slices on top. Enjoy!